From: Bob Paauwe <bob.j.paauwe@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 31 Aug 2015 14:03:30 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 373/435] drm/i915/skl+: Enable pipe CSC on cursor planes.
 (v2)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

commit 'fc6f93bce582ccf76335843584e6a797ac72813c' upstream

Extend this to SKL and BXT as it's needed for these platforms as well.

v2: Change if condition to HAS_DDI() instead of listing each platform
Signed-off-by: Bob Paauwe <bob.j.paauwe@intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Ville Syrjälä <ville.syrjala@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Signed-off-by: Hu <yadi.hu@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c
index 62df3e4..0549898 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c
@@ -9938,7 +9938,7 @@ static void i9xx_update_cursor(struct drm_crtc *crtc, u32 base)
 		}
 		cntl |= pipe << 28; /* Connect to correct pipe */
 
-		if (IS_HASWELL(dev) || IS_BROADWELL(dev))
+		if (HAS_DDI(dev))
 			cntl |= CURSOR_PIPE_CSC_ENABLE;
 	}
 
